This game is so easy it literally has multiple achievements for dying. And I only half joking.
Jokes aside, this game has design choices that contradict each other or don't work at full potential. My opinion in bullet points:
- story doesn't fit the genre. What the point of randomly generated world if story quest hand holds you, always tells where exactly to go and what to do? There is never anything that you don't know in advance about, and you can't find anything "ahead of the story";
- grinding for resources to unlock tiles isn't fun. It makes you feel like a rice- I mean wheat farmer;
- tiles always have exactly what you expect them to have. No point in random. In my opinion, tiles should come in stacks of 10, with quest or special event tiles mixed in. Scrap farming for tiles, add something different to gain tile decks, let build the world in large chunks at once, don't tell players, what they get. Add fog of war to unvisited tiles;
- way too little stuff to "gain" for surviving / exploration game. All you have is story gated upgrades to (two) tools and a house. Game would benefit from more complex production chains. And chopping WHEAT with AXE felt very awkward, to the point that people constantly asking, how to get wheat.
